comments: Banchero (ORL) moves alongside Randle's (NYK) path and briefly rests his arm on Randle's body as marginal contact occurs at the end of the drive.
Okeke (ORL) legally contests Anunoby's (NYK) jump shot attempt.
Anthony (ORL) jumps alongside McBride's (NYK) path and legally contests the driving shot attempt.

After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court (defensive goaltending) was confirmed.  Bitadze (ORL) makes contact with the ball after it has made contact with the backboard and has a chance to score.
Hartenstein (NYK) initiates contact with Bitadze's (ORL) arm, which affects his play at the basket.
Bitadze (ORL) and McBride (NYK) come together at the same spot, and the contact during the drive is marginal.
Fultz (ORL) moves laterally into DiVincenzo's (NYK) path and makes contact with his body, which affects DiVincenzo's shot attempt at the basket.
McBride (NYK) grasps and then quickly releases Anthony's (ORL) jersey as marginal contact occurs before Anthony receives the inbound pass.
DiVincenzo (NYK) brings his hand forward towards the ball, and marginal contact occurs with Fultz's (ORL) arm as he receives the pass.
Hartenstein (NYK) legally contests Carter Jr.'s (ORL) shot attempt in the lane.
Fultz (ORL) pursues the ball and marginal contact occurs with Randle's (NYK) body as he spins away from Fultz during the steal attempt.

Carter Jr. (ORL) and Hartenstein (NYK) briefly engage and disengage as they both pursue the loose ball. After Hartenstein secures possession, Anthony (ORL) makes clean contact with the ball to temporarily dislodge it. Hartenstein then secures the loose ball after he goes to the ground, and the Knicks are granted a timeout.
Okeke (ORL) moves alongside Randle's (NYK) path and maintains a legal guarding position as incidental contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
McBride (NYK) reaches across Banchero (ORL) and makes contact with his arm on the way to the ball, which affects Banchero's ability to make his intended pass.
Isaac (ORL) and Randle (NYK) come together in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Randle (NYK) moves toward Isaac (ORL), who's running in a straight line path, and initiates the marginal body contact as they run up the court.
Banchero (ORL) makes clean contact with the ball as he attempts to steal the ball from Randle (NYK).
Fultz (ORL) avoids making body contact with McBride (NYK) as he contests the jump shot attempt.

Hartenstein (NYK) and Banchero (ORL) simultaneously make clean contact with the ball and Hartenstein dislodges it from Banchero.  The ensuing lower body contact as both players go to the floor is deemed incidental.
Okeke (ORL) legally contests DiVincenzo's (NYK) jump shot attempt.
